@page "/help/getting-started"
@attribute [Authorize]

<PageTitle>Getting Started</PageTitle>

<section class="page-shell">
    <header class="page-header">
        <div>
            <p class="eyebrow">Getting Started</p>
            <h1>Set operators up for a calm, repeatable daily routine.</h1>
        </div>
        <p class="page-intro">
            BrassLedger presents one authenticated workspace with multiple modules. The pages are separate for focus,
            but the balances are connected, so the best start to any day is a disciplined review of the totals and
            queues that matter most.
        </p>
    </header>

    <section class="content-grid">
        <article class="panel">
            <h2>First sign-in checklist</h2>
            <ol class="step-list">
                <li>Sign in and confirm the correct company has loaded.</li>
                <li>Verify the masked tax ID, base currency, and fiscal-year start month.</li>
                <li>Review cash, receivables, payables, payroll, inventory, and projects before posting new work.</li>
                <li>Open the module you use most often and confirm the data looks plausible.</li>
                <li>Record environment issues separately from accounting issues so support work stays clear.</li>
            </ol>
        </article>

        <article class="panel">
            <h2>Suggested daily review order</h2>
            <ol class="step-list">
                <li>Overview for balance health and queue pressure.</li>
                <li>Receivables for incoming cash, past-due items, and customer disputes.</li>
                <li>Payables for due bills, credits, and scheduled payments.</li>
                <li>Operations for open orders, stock pressure, and shipping blockers.</li>
                <li>Payroll for upcoming runs, liabilities, and tax deadlines.</li>
                <li>Reporting for balancing reports before any output is distributed.</li>
            </ol>
        </article>
    </section>

    <section class="panel">
        <h2>Operator expectations</h2>
        <ul class="feature-list">
            <li>Post activity into the module that owns it.</li>
            <li>Use clear references on entries, batches, and adjustments.</li>
            <li>Review reports before exporting or printing final output.</li>
            <li>Escalate suspicious balance changes quickly instead of covering them with manual entries.</li>
            <li>Use the Help pages and guides whenever a workflow, release step, or printed form changes.</li>
        </ul>
    </section>
</section>
